==English==
===Etymology===
First attested in [[w:1340|1340]], from [[Old French]] [[chaméléon]], from [[Latin]] [[chamaeleon]], from [[Greek]] [[khamaileon]], from [[khamai]] ''on the earth; on the ground'' + [[leon]] ''lion''. See also [[chamomile]].
===Alternative spellings===
*[[chamaeleon]]
===Noun===
'''chameleon'''

#A small to mid-size [[reptile]], and one of the best known [[lizard]] families able to change color and project its long tongue.
#A person with inconstant behavior; one able to quickly [[adjust]] to new circumstances.

====Translation====
'''mid-size lizard'''
